19,IssuesEvent,2015-12-16 14:17:34+00:00,2792391,gruns/furl,45051,traut,,,opened,Characters : and @ are not escaped in usernames/passwords,[],[],0,"`@` and `:` are not escaped in result URL when they are present in username/password:

```python
> from furl import furl
> f = furl('http://some-domain.com')
> f.username = 'username@withcharacter'
> f.password = 'complex@password:characters'
> print(f.url)

http://username@withcharacter:complex@password:characters@some-domain.com
```

According to [RFC 3986](http://www.faqs.org/rfcs/rfc3986.html), section 3.2.1, it needs to be percent encoded:
```
  userinfo    = *( unreserved / pct-encoded / sub-delims / "":"" )
```
So it should look like:
```
http://username%40withcharacter:complex%40password%3Acharacters@some-domain.com
```",{},{}
29,IssuesEvent,2017-01-25 15:04:34+00:00,55258005,jopohl/urh,2881532,imaurus,,,opened,Windows compilation error - (errno 2 No such file or directory),[],[],0,"Compilation on Windows 10 gave me this error:

`save_to_xml
    with open(constants.FIELD_TYPE_SETTINGS, ""w"") as f:
FileNotFoundError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: 'C:\\HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\urh\\fieldtypes.xml'`

As workaround I modified ""constants.py"". I changed FIELD_TYPE_SETTINGS to ""fieldtypes.xml"" instead of ""os.path.realpath...blah blah blah""... and now it works.

I guess because QSettings on Windows, NativeFormat settings are stored in the following registry paths:

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\MySoft\Star Runner
HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\MySoft\OrganizationDefaults
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\Software\MySoft\Star Runner
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\Software\MySoft\OrganizationDefaults",{},{}
