1501,IssuesEvent,2017-07-10 15:19:55+00:00,59235,mkleehammer/pyodbc,9948313,dangowrt,,,opened,running on big endian systems,[],[],0,"### Environment

To diagnose, we usually need to know the following, including version numbers.  On Windows, be
sure to specify 32-bit Python or 64-bit:

- MIPS32r2 (big endian)
- Python 3.6.1
- pyodbc 4.0.17
- OS Linux (OpenWrt/LEDE)
- DB PostgreSQL 9.6.3
- driver psqlodbcw (and psqlodbca as well)

### Issue

While everything works nicely on all little endian systems, things break on big-endian boxes:
```
root@LEDE:/# python3
Python 3.6.1 (default, Jul 10 2017, 04:39:25) 
[GCC 5.4.0] on linux
Type ""help"", ""copyright"", ""credits"" or ""license"" for more information.
>>> import pyodbc
>>> cnxn = pyodbc.connect(""DRIVER={PostgreSQL Unicode};SERVER=localhost;DATABASE=template1;UID=postgres;PWD=password;PORT=5432"")
>>> c = cnxn.cursor()
>>> c.execute(""SELECT 'test' AS test"")
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<stdin>"", line 1, in <module>
pyodbc.ProgrammingError: ('42601', '[42601] ERROR: syntax error at or near ""匀䔀䰀䔀䌀吀\u2000✀琀攀猀琀✀\u2000䄀匀\u2000琀攀猀琀"";\nError while executing the query (1) (SQLExecDirectW)')
>>> 
```
Note that ODBC generally works fine on the box, connecting to the same database using `isql` performing the same query is no problem:

```
root@LEDE:/etc# isql psqlodbc_test_dsn
+---------------------------------------+
| Connected!                            |
|                                       |
| sql-statement                         |
| help [tablename]                      |
| quit                                  |
|                                       |
+---------------------------------------+
SQL> SELECT 'test' AS test;
+-----+
| test|
+-----+
| test|
+-----+
SQLRowCount returns 1
1 rows fetched
```

Also note that on an otherwise identical little endian MIPS32r2 it works just fine, ie.
```
root@LEDE:/# python3
imporPython 3.6.1 (default, Jul 10 2017, 09:34:47) 
[GCC 5.4.0] on linux
Type ""help"", ""copyright"", ""credits"" or ""license"" for more information.
        
>>> import pyodbc
>>> cnxn = pyodbc.connect(""DRIVER={PostgreSQL Unicode};SERVER=localhost;DATABASE=template1;UID=postgres;PWD=password;PORT=5432"")
>>> c = cnxn.cursor()
>>> c.execute(""SELECT 'test' AS test"")
<pyodbc.Cursor object at 0x9576d0>
>>> 
```
",{},{}
