1595,IssuesEvent,2017-04-10 20:28:23+00:00,8292338,ultrabug/py3status,852504,lasers,,,opened,Multiline format improvement,[],[],0,"I think if we want to win the hearts and minds of other people with this new formatter thing, we should try and remedy this cosmetic issue first.

```
# purrrrty
    uptime {
        format = '[\?if=weeks {weeks} weeks ][\?if=days {days} days ]
            [\?if=hours {hours} hours ][\?if=minutes {minutes} minutes]'
    }
```
```
# uggggh
    uptime {
        format = '[\?if=weeks {weeks} weeks ][\?if=days {days} days ]'
        format +='[\?if=hours {hours} hours ][\?if=minutes {minutes} minutes]'
    }
```
With `purrrrty`, we get `\n` in the status making it `uggggh`. We should strip them.

This makes it easy for copypasta too with longer formats. Imagine we had lot of `[\?color=#####` in this particular `mpd_status` config... And maybe `max_width` too.
```
# purrrrty
    mpd_status {
        cache_timeout = 5
        format = '[\?if=weeks {weeks} weeks ][\?if=days {days} days ]
            [\?if=hours {hours} hours ][\?if=minutes {minutes} minutes]
            [\?if=hours {hours} hours ][\?if=minutes {minutes} minutes]
            [\?if=hours {hours} hours ][\?if=minutes {minutes} minutes]
            [\?if=hours {hours} hours ][\?if=minutes {minutes} minutes]'
         hide_when_stopped = True
         hide_when_paused = False
    }
```
