1920,IssuesEvent,2016-03-19 00:09:18+00:00,2051226,eligrey/FileSaver.js,217034,evilaliv3,,,opened,Evaluate to implement browsertesting on commit of the demo,[],[],0,"Given the hight usage of the library it would be important to start implementing at least browsertesting of commit of the demo.

This would allow to detect defects happening on some specific browser/version and would make all in possibility to collaborate in the fix; e.g. this would help in solving readly https://github.com/eligrey/FileSaver.js/issues/205, https://github.com/eligrey/FileSaver.js/issues/189, https://github.com/eligrey/FileSaver.js/issues/179, https://github.com/eligrey/FileSaver.js/issues/162, https://github.com/eligrey/FileSaver.js/issues/129

Given the fact that still no unit test is in place i think a good choice could integrate [travis.ci](travis-ci.org) + [grunt](http://gruntjs.com/) + [nightwatch](https://github.com/nightwatchjs/nightwatch) + [saucelabs](https://saucelabs.com/), and the minimum viable product would be to have a browsertesting of the basic demo but executed on the new library result of every commit.

It would be great during the testing to integrate Codeclimate in order to keep track of the code maturity and the code coverage of the tests.

All the softwares i'm suggesting are opensource and the cloud services involved are offering a complete free support for opensource projects so that it would be great if start adopting them as they would allow to do something like the following: https://github.com/ghostbar/angular-zxcvbn/issues/12

e.g.: https://github.com/globaleaks/GlobaLeaks
![screenshot from 2016-03-14 20 36 40](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/217034/13757421/9a540b7e-ea24-11e5-8632-58bef9195fa2.png)",{},{}
