2180,IssuesEvent,2018-01-08 09:53:12+00:00,1017451,gorakhargosh/watchdog,32321592,ehddnr747,,,opened,Missing file event while waiting for other thread's lock.,[],[],0,"I am developing a program which works like 'dropbox' for quite large and complicated file system.

I have two thread in this program.
One is watchdog observer and the other is thread which operates commands for syncing responsively to file_event from observer.

Both thread shares a lock object to keep the order to process.

I overrode 'dispatch' method of FileSystemEventHandler class to toss event to another thread.
Inside this method, it tries to get lock before dispatch, otherwise it waits.

I start program with initial_sync method, which takes quite time and it locks other thread.

What I expect is that file_events during initial_sync should wait for the end of initial_sync due to lock,
and will be processed after initial_sync is done.

But the result from my test seems it misses file_events during initial_sync.
Initial_sync typically takes 2 hours and the size of syncing is around 200GB.

I am not sure whether there is timeout for return of 'dispatch' method.
Is it? Is this intended?
Then how can I escape this situation?
Or is there any reason for this symptom?",{},{}
2186,IssuesEvent,2017-11-16 08:03:41+00:00,24561828,gunthercox/ChatterBot,17780397,pramodpm,,,opened,Custom adapter not returning values,[],[],0,"I am using Chatterbot 0.7.6 version. I want to integrate a custom logic adapter which will get activated based on a special character at the start of statement(^).  I want to retrieve some values for local Solr search when there is a special character. Otherwise I want to use the other logic adapters.

