",{},{}
2543,IssuesEvent,2018-07-02 14:12:35+00:00,1778869,jsocol/django-ratelimit,94505,phillbaker,,,opened,Rate limit on URL parameters?,[],[],0,"Thanks for your work on this library!

Parameters captured by Django's URLconf are passed into the view function as parameters, e.g.:

```py
# urls.py
url(regex=r'^user/(?P<username>\w{1,50})/$', view='views.profile_page')

# views.py
def profile_page(request, username=None):
    user = User.objects.get(username=username)
   # ...
```

These parameters are available on the request object itself (or in `request.{GET,POST,META}`), what would be the recommended approach to rate limit on these parameters?",{},{}
