2660,IssuesEvent,2018-08-01 18:36:49+00:00,53352663,ecederstrand/exchangelib,96759,mdoar,,,closed,Performance of searching for oldest message,[],[],6,"v1.11.4
I run the following filter
`msgs = account.inbox.all().filter(datetime_received__gt=start_date).filter(is_read=False).order_by('datetime_received')`

and the expected results are returned quickly. 

But when I try to access the oldest message with
`oldest_msg = msg[0]`

then the execution time of the last line depends greatly on whether the oldest message is a few messages ago, or if it is hundreds of messages ago. 

For example, if there are two unread messages and both are recent, the time is less than a second. But if there two unread messages are many messages apart, then the time can be 15 seconds.

Is there a better approach to retrieving oldest messages? I've tried using a slice [:10] of all the msgs, I've considered using Only. But I think there must be some approach I've missed.",{},{}
