2716,IssuesEvent,2017-04-05 09:23:28+00:00,26828443,trustrachel/python-ntlm3,1426678,redskins80,,,opened,NTLM auth value not decoded properly. Value contains 'b//',[],[],0,"While authenticating via NTLM, the NTLM_NEGOTIATE message at `ntlm3.HTTPNtlmAuthHandler.AbstractNtlmAuthHandler.retry_using_http_NTLM_auth`, line no 57, contains a leading `'b//` and a trailing '//'. This is also happening at line no 107 where the NTLM message is authenticated.

