3028,IssuesEvent,2018-08-05 04:41:26+00:00,68146968,vimalloc/flask-jwt-extended,19337791,christian-quisbert,,,opened,"Correct ""an expire flag"" ",[],[],0,"https://github.com/vimalloc/flask-jwt-extended/blob/3d598d401d06aa959cdca33c9e63b4c6ad64b98e/examples/redis_blacklist.py#L85

**L85 and L86 are incorrect.**

This 2 lines should be:
` revoked_store.set(access_jti, 'false', timedelta(seconds=ACCESS_EXPIRES.total_seconds() + 600)
`
`
revoked_store.set(refresh_jti, 'false', timedelta(seconds=REFRESH_EXPIRES.total_seconds() + 600)
`
In this way, for example, the tokens are revoked 10 minute after they expired.


