3325,IssuesEvent,2017-02-23 13:35:38+00:00,48501841,django/daphne,725049,cbay,27804,django,opened,parse_x_forwarded_for fails with IPv6 addresses,[],[],0,"When `X-Forwarded-Proto` contains an IPv6 (e.g. `2001:db8:85a3::8a2e:370:7334`), it raises the following traceback:

```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""/home/foo/env/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/daphne/http_protocol.py"", line 77, in process
    self.client_addr
  File ""/home/foo/env/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/daphne/utils.py"", line 37, in parse_x_forwarded_for
    address_host, address_port = address_value.split(':')
ValueError: too many values to unpack
```

Since `X-Forwarded-Proto` is not standard, I don't have a sane suggestion on how to handle both IPv6 and ports. It seems that IPv6 is much more common than including the port in that header. For instance:

* AWS: http://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/classic/x-forwarded-headers.html#x-forwarded-for
* Cloudflare: https://support.cloudflare.com/hc/en-us/articles/200170986-How-does-Cloudflare-handle-HTTP-Request-headers-

I'm using nginx, for the record.",{},{}
