3784,IssuesEvent,2016-09-26 08:27:35+00:00,14993021,ipython/traitlets,151929,minrk,230453,ipython,closed,"Enhance `--help-all` to print all relevant  configurables, along with their relations",[],[],3,"Now that an elaborate traversal of **""Configurable-inheritance""**  got merged (#289) for when generating the sample config-file (hopefully everything works all right),
is there a reason why the same logic is not used when printing the `--help-all`  message?
(i.e. to reduce the clutter in the terminal?)

Specifically in [traitlets/config/application.py#L384](https://github.com/ipython/traitlets/blob/master/traitlets/config/application.py#L384) where the classes to examine gets decided, there is this line:

    help_classes = self.classes

I would expect to find:

    help_classes =  = self._classes_inc_parents(self)  

but I've tested with even with the new `self._classes_in_config_sample()` method and it works fine.

A PR for this would be trivial, but now that `parent` is appropriately set on sub-commands (#292),
~~we can~~ *it may be possible to*  traverse the **""commands-chain""**, to provide also hints about them on the help & sample-config-file sections, like that:  

    [root-cmd  previous-sub-cmd]  *sub-cmd(parent1, parent2)

[*] It is the `sub-cmd` that is documented above.
",{},{}
