4088,IssuesEvent,2015-01-19 11:34:29+00:00,1126087,gitpython-developers/GitPython,63622,Byron,503709,gitpython-developers,closed,Implement new submodule handling,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gitpython-developers/GitPython/labels/acknowledged', 'name': 'acknowledged', 'color': '02e10c'}]",[],2,"In previous git versions, it was common to checkout submodules right at the spot in the tree of their parent repository.

In later git versions though, submodule repositories are placed outside of the working tree.

Git-python should choose the submodule mode depending on the python version, and thus remain backwards compatible.",{},{}
4093,IssuesEvent,2017-12-01 17:00:53+00:00,1126087,gitpython-developers/GitPython,787332,theckman,503709,gitpython-developers,opened,New GitPython release to include changes fixed in #689,[],[],0,"Hi @Byron,

Thank you so much for your hard work on coordinating the efforts of this project. I've run in to the issue fixed by #689, and subsequently noticed comment about getting a new release ready:

* https://github.com/gitpython-developers/GitPython/pull/689#issuecomment-345523032

I definitely don't want to come across as trying to prescribe how to organize your project and releases, and I understand that there are some things to be done for the next release. To make it a little easier for you, I wonder if you'd be willing to release a `v2.1.8` that includes only the changes in #689?

If your preference is to finish the other things first, no sweat and I'm happy to wait for the next release I only wanted to open an issue that any of us who are affected can follow so we can get an email when the next is release pushed out. :)

Thank you again for your time and work on GitPython.",{},{}
