```

</details><br>

**Reproduction**

(I haven't found the time yet to create a distilled reproduction case or look into what might be causing this exactly; so, currently getting to the actual failing test involves quite a few downloads)

In a clean Python 3.6 virtualenv, run the following script:

```sh
# Get the code
git clone https://github.com/pradyunsg/pip.git
cd pip
git checkout a1f1792870cce2f78218088f3ea31aead300d585
# Alternatively, download and unpack
# https://github.com/pradyunsg/pip/archive/a1f1792870cce2f78218088f3ea31aead300d585.zip

# Prepare the testing environment
pip install -r tools/tests-requirements.txt
pip install .

# Run the tests such that it invokes monkeytype 
# Here we run only one test, to ensure this isn't happening because of some sort of
# race condition or interaction of multiple instances.
pytest ""tests/functional/test_install_wheel.py::test_basic_install_from_wheel""
```

**Additional Context**
Note that pip's test suite does a lot of things that might make this a little difficult to debug -- almost every creates a new temporary venv from a template venv (this ensures isolation between tests) and installs pip in the new temporary venv which is then invoked via a subprocess that in turn, runs pip with monkeytype collection enabled.",{},{}
