4410,IssuesEvent,2017-05-28 01:12:47+00:00,1928051,selectel/pyte,185856,superbobry,804735,selectel,opened,Known rendering quirks,"[{'id': 558397541, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/selectel/pyte/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'b60205', 'default': True}, {'id': 558397477, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/selectel/pyte/labels/help-wanted', 'name': 'help-wanted', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}]",[],0,"This is an incomplete list of apps which are known to be rendered incorrectly with `TERM=linux`. Every quirk in the list potentially indicates a bug in one of the `Screen` method. These bugs are notoriously hard to pin down, but if you're feeling brave -- contributions are more than welcome!

* `emacs --no-init-file` and `M-x tetris`
* `man man` does not highlight the occurence during searching
* `vi` endlessly triggers `Screen.report_device_attributes`

To validate the quirk start `webterm.py`

```bash
$ PYTHONPATH=. python webterm.py
```

and type the corresponding command.",{},{}
4414,IssuesEvent,2015-05-27 14:41:29+00:00,5088232,segmentio/analytics-python,649671,greghball,819518,segmentio,opened,debug option to client works oddly (and doesn't work in python2.6),[],[],0,"When you create an instance of the `Client` class and pass `debug=True`, the `__init__` method will execute

    self.log.setLevel('DEBUG')

and there are 2 problems with this.

1) `self.log` is the logger instance named 'segment' - it's the same instance for every client, so if you create multiple clients you can't use different values for `debug` or things get confused.

2) In python 2.6, you can't say `log.setLevel('DEBUG')`, you have to say `log.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)`, otherwise you're effectively setting the log level to an arbitrary high level and no log messages appear.

Is python 2.6 supported? I can't find any documentation that specifies either way. ",{},{}
