5487,IssuesEvent,2016-04-19 03:20:15+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,242750,tseaver,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,closed,dns.Client.zone lacks a description parameter.,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/dns', 'name': 'dns', 'color': '5319e7'}]",[],2,"The `description` parameter is required to the API call to `manageZones.create`, however, this parameter is not exposed in `Client.zone`. This leads to the awkward pattern:

```python
zone = client.zone('zone-name', dns_name='example.com.')
zone.description = 'My zone'
zone.create()
```

Where it should be:

```python
zone = client.zone('zone-name', dns_name='example.com.', description='My zone')
zone.create()
```",{},{}
