5858,IssuesEvent,2016-06-08 04:02:28+00:00,12164337,googledrive/PyDrive,10717566,RNabel,3708359,googledrive,closed,Installing pydrive through Pip causes an error,[],[],1,"When importing PyDrive, after installing with the command `sudo -H pip install -t ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages"" PyDrive`, the import fails when attempting to import a PyDrive dependency, `httplib2`.

This issue has probably risen due to not porting PyDrive to Python3...

Wouldn't it just be viable to use `lib2to3` to convert it all to Py3?",{},{}
5868,IssuesEvent,2016-03-24 14:26:38+00:00,25285581,datamade/parserator,1406537,cathydeng,3723931,datamade,opened,guidelines for reporting parsing issues for usaddress/probablepeople,[],[],0,"would be nice to add guidelines (in web interface, readmes, & documentation) so that we are not having the same conversations over and over on github. maybe a link to an issue template?

- real strings from real data
