6071,IssuesEvent,2017-04-06 08:43:08+00:00,10247874,docker/docker-py,13072423,qq690388648,5429470,docker,opened,Why does the 'cpuset_mems' only can be set when update?,[],[],0,"I find that the `cpuset_mems` only exist in the parameter of `update` method(https://github.com/docker/docker-py/blob/830b9edce8691440e571270488e7bfa803e62d2d/docker/models/containers.py#L381, https://github.com/docker/docker-py/blob/830b9edce8691440e571270488e7bfa803e62d2d/docker/api/container.py#L1170), but does not exist in the parameter of `HostConfig`'s constructor(https://github.com/docker/docker-py/blob/830b9edce8691440e571270488e7bfa803e62d2d/docker/types/containers.py#L119).

PS: The `HostConfig`'s constructor has `cpuset_cpus`, so I don't think the `cpuset_mems` is missing unintentionally.",{},{}
