6101,IssuesEvent,2015-03-04 04:05:08+00:00,12968651,pgmpy/pgmpy,2332955,abinashpanda,5500131,pgmpy,opened,Sepset beliefs in BeliefPropagation,[],[],0,"At present, in the ```BeliefPropagation``` class, the sepset beliefs are stored in the form of a dictionary with key as the sepset between the two sets. This has a serious issues with some graphs. For example: Consider a junction tree with nodes ```(A, B, C) --- (A, D) --- (A, E)```. The sepsets would be ```A``` in all the cases so the key is no longer unique.",{},{}
