6356,IssuesEvent,2018-03-27 03:12:45+00:00,77478378,ethereum/py-evm,9263930,hwwhww,6250754,ethereum,closed,SMC (VMC): No more empty slots,"[{'id': 769749869, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ethereum/py-evm/labels/Sharding', 'name': 'Sharding', 'color': 'f2e346', 'default': False}]",[],1,"### What is wrong?
@justindrake came up with a solution for that we can obsolete the ""empty slots"" in the collator list.

### How can it be fixed
1. Add another mapping for `collator_address` -> `pool_index`, the collator can use the address to look up the index by address.
1. In the `withdraw` function, after the collator was removed from the pool, there's a new empty slot. Now we move the last element to fill the slot immediately and update the mapping of (1).

Please wait for the new specification with new namings.",{},{}
