6523,IssuesEvent,2015-10-26 19:48:29+00:00,26839425,arista-eosplus/pyeapi,7631359,phil-arista,6643264,arista-eosplus,opened,[API BGP] _parse_shutdown can't accurately determine shutdown state,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/arista-eosplus/pyeapi/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],0,"The parse was using a simple check for 'no neighbor NAME shutdown'.  This isn't satisfactory.  The neighbor can be active, or idle and the configuration omits 'no neighbor NAME shutdown'  This was causing pyeapi to report the neighbor was shutdown when it really isn't.  Some more research needs to be done here since there's also a shutdown state for the peer_group (if you add the neighbor to it).",{},{}
6526,IssuesEvent,2017-10-26 09:24:11+00:00,26829379,VUnit/vunit,4130208,dave2pi,6691399,VUnit,opened,"Modelsim: Invalid value for generic ""output_path"".  Not using this value.",[],[],0,"Since commit [76d17d5](https://github.com/VUnit/vunit/commit/76d17d5f85d24de7686c67431e126972228886fc) ""Added human readable test output paths. #211"" `config_name`'s containing commas can be passed to Modelsim as part of the top level generic `output_path` and Modelsim doesn't seem to like commas.

If I run the vunit example from `vunit\examples\vhdl\generate_tests` (and I run it from C:\ to avoid any windows path length issues) I'm getting the following error:
I'm running ModelSim PE 10.5c Jul 21 2016
(output abbreviated)
```bash
C:\generate_tests>python run.py --version
2.2.0
C:\generate_tests>python run.py --clean
Compiling...
Starting lib.tb_generated.data_width=1,sign=False.Test 1
# vsim -modelsimini C:/generate_tests/vunit_out/modelsim/modelsim.ini -wlf C:/generate_tests/vunit_out/test_output/lib.tb_generated.data_width=1,sign=False.Test_1_b8881b8ddd543fcd90d8901c4daae75a83945267/modelsim/vsim.wlf -quiet -t ps -onfinish stop lib.tb_generated(a) -L vunit_lib -L lib -g/tb_generated/runner_cfg=""active python runner : true,enabled_test_cases : Test 1,output path : C::/generate_tests/vunit_out/test_output/lib.tb_generated.data_width=1,,sign=False.Test_1_b8881b8ddd543fcd90d8901c4daae75a83945267/,tb path : C::/generate_tests/test/"" -g/tb_generated/output_path=C:/generate_tests/vunit_out/test_output/lib.tb_generated.data_width=1,sign=False.Test_1_b8881b8ddd543fcd90d8901c4daae75a83945267/ -g/tb_generated/sign=False -g/tb_generated/data_width=1 -g/tb_generated/message=set-for-entity
# Start time: 09:24:39 on Oct 26,2017
# //  ModelSim PE 10.5c Jul 21 2016
# ** Warning: (vsim-3351) Invalid value ""C:/generate_tests/vunit_out/test_output/lib.tb_generated.data_width=1,sign=False.Test_1_b8881b8ddd543fcd90d8901c4daae75a83945267/"" for generic ""output_path"".  Not using this value.
#    Time: 0 ps  Iteration: 0  Instance: /tb_generated File: C:/generate_tests/test/tb_generated.vhd
# ** Fatal: (vsim-3350) Generic ""output_path"" has not been given a value.
#    Time: 0 ps  Iteration: 0  Instance: /tb_generated File: C:/generate_tests/test/tb_generated.vhd Line: 15
# FATAL ERROR while loading design
# Error loading design
Error loading design
# End time: 09:24:41 on Oct 26,2017, Elapsed time: 0:00:02
# Errors: 1, Warnings: 1
fail (P=0 S=0 F=1 T=9) lib.tb_generated.data_width=1,sign=False.Test 1 (4.9 seconds)
```

If I change the config_name formatting in `generate_tests/run.py` from:
`config_name = ""data_width=%i,sign=%s"" % (data_width, sign)`
to
`config_name = ""data_width=%i.sign=%s"" % (data_width, sign)`
without a comma, then modelsim accepts it.

Alternatively if I edit `vunit/test_runner.py` to include comma as an illegal char:
`ILLEGAL_CHARS = ' <>""|:*%?\\/#&;(),'`
it also now works.

I noticed this issue when I tried to rerun some test sets I wrote back in June in which I was formatting the config_name in the same comma seperated style as the generate_tests example. Replacing `,` with `.` in these fixes them as well.

VUnit 2.0.2rc0 works fine since the paths only contain a hash
VUnit 2.2.0 doesn't work
VUnit 2.2.1rc0 doesn't work

Has anybody else noticed this?",{},{}
