6563,IssuesEvent,2017-08-29 16:20:02+00:00,9801644,elastic/elasticsearch-py,132113,robx,6764390,elastic,opened,`indices.exists` is misleading with wildcard indices,[],[],0,"Since `indices.exists(ix)` is more or less defined to be `HEAD /ix == 20x`, `indices.exists(""*"")` always returns true, even if there are no indices. I see two sensible things to do here, maybe there are others?

1. change `indices.exists` to return `len(GET /ix)` (at least if wildcards are involved)
2. document this behaviour explicitly (that using `indices.exists` with wildcard indices is not what you're likely to want, and recommend to call `len(indices.get())` instead",{},{}
