6698,IssuesEvent,2016-09-25 23:51:10+00:00,39039065,Azure/azure-storage-python,6854498,pemari-msft,6844498,Azure,closed,PUBLIC NOTICE: Azure Storage Python 0.30 Release,[],[],2,"We are pleased to announce the 0.30 preview release of the [Azure Storage Python Client Library](https://github.com/Azure/azure-storage-python/). With this version comes all features included in the 2015-04-05 REST version including support for the following features:
- Append Blob support
- File service support
- Lazy Enumeration for listing APIs
- Account SAS support
- Table Batch refactors
- JSON Table formatting support

The team has worked to address many of the customer concerns and gaps to bring it up parity with our other libraries. Please see our [Getting Started Docs](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/?service=storage&platform=python) to check out all of these new features. The 0.30 release has many breaking changes, so to help transition from older versions of the library please review our [latest reference documentation](http://azure.github.io/azure-storage-python/), [upgrade guide](http://azure.github.io/azure-storage-python/upgrade.html), [usage samples](https://github.com/Azure/azure-storage-python/tree/master/samples) and [Breaking Changes](https://github.com/Azure/azure-storage-python/blob/master/BreakingChanges.md) log.
As always, we will continue to do our work in the public GitHub dev branch for visibility and transparency. Please let us know if you have any concerns or suggestions with the new library as community feedback is very important to us.

Thank you,
The Azure Storage Team",{},{}
