6904,IssuesEvent,2017-09-25 11:49:35+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,5611123,wstomv,7388996,jupyter,opened,Copy paste between notebooks and execution count,[],[],0,"When copy pasting cells between notebooks, everything is copied over:

* source
* outputs
* `execution_count` (which is shown as `In[#]`)

This may result in a notebook with code cells that have **_duplicate_ execution counts**.
This in turn can be confusing, especially when using IPython features to refer back
to execution results using output history (`_`, `__`, `___`, `_oh`).

Of course, a similar situation can arise when you restart the kernel, without deleting all output, or rerunning all cells.",{},{}
