7533,IssuesEvent,2017-04-05 10:19:08+00:00,46293472,Backblaze/B2_Command_Line_Tool,1674237,Elusive138,10283486,Backblaze,opened,Missing characters when syncing root,[],[],0,"With an attempt at syncing root, e.g. `b2 sync / b2://foo/bar`, a character is missing in the path resulting in errors such as:

```
OSError: [Errno 2] No such file or directory: '/in/bash'
```

Which somehow found `/in/bash` instead of `/bin/bash`.

I believe this is because the attempt at calculating prefix length in [folder.py:79](https://github.com/Backblaze/B2_Command_Line_Tool/blob/0308d37e5cc92765064118b38abccd35351bfd11/b2/sync/folder.py#L79) fails to take into account the root path `/`, where there is no _trailing_ slash as such.

A quick fix might be to special-case root, but to be honest the whole prefix calculation looks pretty fragile.",{},{}
