7804,IssuesEvent,2018-06-29 06:08:59+00:00,70920962,PyFilesystem/pyfilesystem2,4391664,xandfury,11898830,PyFilesystem,closed,How to modify Info attributes,[],[],7,"Hi there. Thanks for `pyfilesystem2`! 

We at [Conpot](https://github.com/mushorg/conpot/) are trying to create an effective sandbox system that could handle malware uploads. For the same, I need to fake changes in file owners/permissions etc. Wondering if that is possible using `fs`

For example:
```python
>>> test = tempfs.TempFS('')
>>> test.listdir('.')
[]
>>> test.settext('README.md', ""Tetris clone"")
>>> test.listdir('/')
['README.md']
>>> test.getinfo('./README.md', namespaces=['access']).get('access', 'user')
'test_user'
```
Now I want to change the `owner` of `README.md` file. [I read the docs](https://docs.pyfilesystem.org/en/latest/reference/base.html#fs.base.FS.setinfo) and this is what I have tried so far:

```python
>>> # trying to change the file owner to 'conpot'
>>> change_user = {'access': {'permissions': ['g_r', 'g_w', 'o_r', 'u_r', 'u_w'], 'uid': 1000, 'gid': 1000, 'group': 'conpot', 'user': 'conpot'}, 'basic': {'is_dir': False, 'name': 'README.md'}}
>>> test.setinfo('./README.md', change_user)
>>> # this doesn't work however.
>>> test.getinfo('./README.md', namespaces=['access']).get('access', 'user')
'test_user'


>>> # I have also tried
>>> resource_info = test.getinfo('.', namespaces=['details', 'access'])
>>> resource_info.user = 'conpot'
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<input>"", line 1, in <module>
AttributeError: can't set attribute
```
How do I go about modifying file owner?

Navigating the code, I did come accross [this](https://github.com/PyFilesystem/pyfilesystem2/blob/95a2f5ae0ae42dfe9f0b7acb2ced58aa234fc0ae/fs/info.py#L133). Apparently there are `writeable` namespaces. Not sure if I can modify attributes though.  ",{},{}
