8135,IssuesEvent,2016-10-07 16:59:44+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,11270809,srware,14095512,IntelRealSense,opened,Understanding librealsense Releases,[],[],0,"Looking for the right librealsense release on github is the most confusing thing I have seen in weeks.

There seem to be a number of releases running in parallel from both the development branch and master branch with slightly different names (like for ZR300) but there is also a 1.10.0 version being released before 1.9.7 and a couple of times there have been multiple releases of the same version but to a later commit.

