8583,IssuesEvent,2017-04-18 20:15:30+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6504915,bmw,17889013,certbot,opened,Print deprecation warning on experimental systems in certbot-auto,"[{'id': 276243379, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/area:%20certbot-auto', 'name': 'area: certbot-auto', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}, {'id': 277080619, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/area:%20code%20health', 'name': 'area: code health', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}, {'id': 276667632, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/area:%20pkging', 'name': 'area: pkging', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}]",[],0,"We have a number of systems where we have ""experimental"" bootstrap support but we have OS packages available. We should print a deprecation warning for these systems telling users that support is going away including how to install the OS packages. We will be removing support completely for these systems in a few months. The current experimental systems are:

* Mageia
* Manjaro 
* Gentoo
* FreeBSD
* macOS
* Amazon Linux
* Joyent SmartOS Zone

At the very least, Gentoo, FreeBSD, and macOS have other options but we should check out other systems as well.",{},{}
8599,IssuesEvent,2018-05-14 17:33:00+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6504915,bmw,17889013,certbot,closed,config_changes uses a messed up non-pager,"[{'id': 200596079, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/area:%20ui%20/%20ux', 'name': 'area: ui / ux', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}, {'id': 149596829, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/good%20first%20issue', 'name': 'good first issue', 'color': 'c61aff', 'default': True}]",[],3,"If you have more than one page full of output from the `config_changes` subcommand, you will get the last page listed with a weird ""Press Enter to Continue"" prompt.

Probably what that command should do if stdout is a terminal is invoke `$PAGER` to list the changes, in the same way that `git log` does. But failing that it should just output the stream of data so the user can pipe it to their preferred pager.",{},{}
8630,IssuesEvent,2018-07-16 16:43:43+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,66133,karsthammer,17889013,certbot,opened,certbot-dns-google: Allow manually specifying the project id,[],[],0,"Currently certbot-dns-google only has the option of getting the project from the service account JSON or from the instance metadata. It would be nice if it would accept the project as a command line argument overriding these defaults.

Our setup consists of a Google Cloud setup with multiple projects. Servers can be in a different project than the project where we host the DNS.

Example:

* Project A has our DNS zone example.com
* Project B has a server X for which we need a certificate (x.example.com)

We create a service account in project B, to that service account we assign the correct permissions (in project A!). Because the service account is in project B and the server is in project B, certbot fails to find the dns zone.

This would be solved by allowing to manually specify the project where the dns zone is located.
",{},{}
