This is a minor problem spotted in the wild while testing raiden.

It can happen that a settling event is processed two times and that by the time the second greenlet gets to the `set_settled()` function then `settled_block` is already set. This will currently throw a `RuntimeError` in the greenlet as seen below:

```
INFO:raiden.event_handler       state_change received state_change=<raiden.transfer.mediated_transfer.state_change.ContractReceiveSettled object at 0x7fcf38adeb90>                                                                                                              
INFO:raiden.event_handler       state_change received state_change=<raiden.transfer.mediated_transfer.state_change.ContractReceiveSettled object at 0x7fcf38adedd0>                                                                                                              
ERROR:raiden.tasks      unexpected exception on alarm                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
Traceback (most recent call last):                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/tasks.py"", line 106, in poll_for_new_block                                                                                                                                                                                               
    result = callback(current_block)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/raiden_service.py"", line 351, in poll_blockchain_events                                                                                                                                                                                  
    on_statechange(state_change)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/event_handler.py"", line 219, in on_blockchain_statechange                                       
    self.handle_settled(state_change)                                                                     
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/event_handler.py"", line 288, in handle_settled                                                  
    channel.state_transition(state_change)                                               
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/channel/netting_channel.py"", line 834, in state_transition                                      
    self.external_state.set_settled(state_change.block_number)                    
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/channel/netting_channel.py"", line 93, in set_settled                                            
    % (self._settled_block, block_number)                               
RuntimeError: channel is already settled on different block 1538047 1538048                                                             
INFO:raiden.network.protocol    MESSAGE RECEIVED node:25511699 echohash:231cc595 <Ping [msghash=bd8c58c4]>                              
INFO:raiden.message_handler     message received message=<Ping [msghash=bd8c58c4]>                                                      
INFO:raiden.network.protocol    SENDING ACK 25511699 > 9bed7fd1 <Ack [echohash:231cc595]>                                               
DEBUG:raiden.tasks      new block timestamp=1503476827.65 number=1538049                                                                
INFO:raiden.event_handler       state_change received state_change=<raiden.transfer.mediated_transfer.state_change.ContractReceiveSettled object at 0x7fcf38b389d0>                                                                                                              
ERROR:raiden.tasks      unexpected exception on alarm                             
Traceback (most recent call last):                                                       
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/tasks.py"", line 106, in poll_for_new_block                                                      
    result = callback(current_block)                                              
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/raiden_service.py"", line 351, in poll_blockchain_events                                         
    on_statechange(state_change)                                                                          
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/event_handler.py"", line 219, in on_blockchain_statechange                                       
    self.handle_settled(state_change)                                                    
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/event_handler.py"", line 288, in handle_settled                                                  
    channel.state_transition(state_change)                                                                
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/channel/netting_channel.py"", line 834, in state_transition                                      
    self.external_state.set_settled(state_change.block_number)                           
  File ""/home/lefteris/ew/raiden/raiden/channel/netting_channel.py"", line 93, in set_settled                                            
    % (self._settled_block, block_number)                                                                 
RuntimeError: channel is already settled on different block 1538047 1538048                                 
```

## Solution

The runtime exception is not harmful but it looks bad and since it can happen in the wild the logic should be changed to return `False` and have the greenlet's event processing stop at that point with a `log.warn()`.",{},{}
