8781,IssuesEvent,2017-08-15 13:27:20+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,Shortcut for `%preview --limit` to show all rows,[],[],1,"Currently --limit is default to 200 rows. I tried to use `--limit -1` to show all rows (vtools convention) but it shows all but the last row. `--limit -2` will show all but the last 2 rows, etc. Is there a shorthand to show all rows? Shall we make behavior of negative `--limit` well defined?",{},{}
8786,IssuesEvent,2017-09-08 02:24:18+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,917985,gaow,20074389,vatlab,opened,[global] section scope,[],[],0,"Separated from #802 

This scope issue with `[global]` often bothers me. What I usually do in research is to prototype using some local cells with loose SoS statements, and after my codes are tested I put them to formal steps to execute. This inevitably involves using global variables in both inside and outside steps. With the current SoS implemention I usually find myself having to define one same variable twice: one under [global] to let workflows use them, one as a local statement for interactive analysis. It would be great if we can make this part easier. 

",{},{}
